	   <tr><td colspan=2>Very few Shadow Knights realize just how powerful they are.&nbsp;&nbsp;Forget what everyone seems to say, use your pet.  But use your pet as a DOT, do not try to use your pet the way a Necromancer uses his pet.  You are a Shadow Knight, you have more HP and more AC and more combat skills than a Necromancer.  If a Necromancer had our HP and AC they wouldn't need a pet as powerful as they have now.  Sure your pet isn't going to be hitting for any major damage, and it's going to be missing a lot, but so what.  It does hit, it does do damage, and every little bit of damage helps.  Just make sure to turn the pet taunt off so the mob focuses on you.<br><br>As for which weapons to specialize in, you would be foolish not to master every weapon skill.  The method I used was to work them all evenly, so at 12th level they were all 51+.  It wasn't easy, but now at 15th lvl, the skills rise very fast.  At 20th all will be at master level.  This is my second SK.  My first was a Dark Elf which I played to 50 before quitting EQ for a while.  This current SK is a Troll, and it is much easier to play than the DE.  <br><br>My point is to use ALL of your powers, and don't listen to people that a skill of yours is useless.  I've never lost a fight to a warrior or a paladin because I take advantage of that green &quot;useless&quot; pet.  If you're a warrior or Paladin and doubt me, feel free to look me up on Cazic Thule.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
