<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=103458481722403></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f103458481722403><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=5&mid=103458481722403>RE: Let the Pet Die?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=5&mid=103458481722403#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=145263><span id=Scholar>lunaticfringesk</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>177 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Oct 14th 4:58 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.10]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Your pet should be viewed as a DoT; nothing more.&nbsp;&nbsp;It will be so many levels behind both you and the mobs you are facing, you never want it tanking unless you are trying to flee, in which case it can be a great distraction.  You never want your pet, as an SK, to be tanking, as it will die very quickly.<br><br>Not sure if someone recommended to you to have your pet tank til death and then you rush in to finish it off, but that is probably not a very good battle strategy.  It makes little sense to waste both mana and bone chips to continue to re-summon your pet over and over.<br><br>You should seldom, if ever, have your pet up if you are the puller, especially in &quot;higher&quot; level zones, for as soon as you are &quot;hit,&quot; your pet will charge in, generally screwing up everything.<br><br>Pets are ok for fear-kiting though.  Even then sometimes they can be a pain in the arse.<br><br>I can tell you that more often than not I do not have my pet up.  As a matter of fact, I only bring him out when, for some reason, I (or the grp) am trying to squeeze out every bit of damage we can.  <br><br>I think that SK pets are definitely underused.  Paradoxically, however, I just dont use mine all that much.  I dont know if I just get lazy or what, but life is definitely a lot easier without them.  In other words, the pain of bringing them out sometimes just outweighs the additoinal damage that they bring.  <br><br>This is not to suggest that they add an immaterial amount of damage.  No.  SKs far too often underestimate how much damage they actually do, which isnt too bad at all.<br><br>I guess i just get lazy when I think about it  =)<br><br>Also, on an unrelated note, SKs spells at higher levels DEFINITELY are very useful and WILL do significant amounts of damage, particularily to the high level Luclin mobs that have a ton of ac.  In those cases, a 338 HP tap packs quite a punch, especially when your dmg 40+ weapon is hitting for crapola.<br><br>Luna<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
