<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=103457069021332></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f103457069021332><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=5&mid=103457069021332>RE: Let the Pet Die?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=5&mid=103457069021332#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=631><span id=Guru>Sir Parttime</span></a>, <span id=Guru>Guru</span><br><span id=notbold>122 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Oct 14th 1:02 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.30]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Greting Laz...<br><br>A few of things.&nbsp;&nbsp;First, your pet will not take any experience from you as long as you do at least 1 point of damage yourself.  If your pet does all the damage to a MOB (Doubtful in the case of the Shadow Knight) you will only take half experience.  In a group, a pet will never take any experience.  This issue was adressed in the caster balancing and sort of help us Shadow Knights as well (Although it was probably an accident).<br><br>If you are &quot;Fear Kiting&quot; properly, your pet will not die since the mob is constantly running from you and not beating on you or your pet very much.  That being the case, your pet is one of the most mana efficient DOTs that we have as a class.<br><br>I agree with the poster who said to use your pet buff.  It is not great but every bit of DPS is good.<br><br>A couple other things that were addressed is that your pet will ALWAYS be the highest possible level pet that you can cast.  Meaning that if your pet's level offically ranges from 9 - 12th level, you will always raise a 12th level pet.<br><br>Lastly, your pet will not aggro stuff anymore just because it is green to all the wondering Mobs.  This was a major hassel in the past because you were often having to kill green mobs that thought they could kill your pet, but knew they had no chance of killing you. Again, this issue was fixed within the last 6 months or so.  The only time your pet will aggro something is if attacking another of the Mob's friends.<br><br>I hope this helps...<br>&nbsp;<br>Shrikke - Knight of Fear<br>Bristlebane</td></tr>
