	   <tr><td colspan=2>Greetings Luna,<br><br>I completely agree with you about the time commitment to get to 60th.&nbsp;&nbsp;Heck, Shrikke is just 45th level and I have been playing him since Kunark's release.  However, I am not sure I am of the opinion that the point of the game is to get to the +55th level.  If that is the case, then the best advice is to either get a character via EBay or two box a Shadow Knight and a Shammy.<br><br>I took the original's poster's question as &quot;I have not learned how to play my class because I am too twinked...what is the best method to get that experience?&quot;  Of course, &quot;Fearing&quot; a second Mob when you are engaged with another is risky and often fatal, Shadow Step is unpredictable and FD is a lot better method post 30th...if you have managed to sit around and cast the cold buff for and hour or so to get that skill up.  However, the benchmark of an excellent Shadow Knight is being able to use the tools at our disposal with a clear idea of how they work and get out of situations that mean death to just about any other class.  If you don't use your tools, the lessons of how to use them properly will never come.  <br><br>My point is that the idea of twinking a character and doing the ring from OT, DL, to Velk's to 60th without putting yourself into some situation that are flat dangerous and scary are going to produce Shadow Knights with the skills of those mindless Warriors you seem to distain.  (However, I think that most Warriors would not be impressed with being called mindless.)<br><br>I have not played the 55+ level game yet.  I do know the game for Shadow Knights changes dramatically at those levels.  However, I am sure that if you can't use the tools you are given to begin with that you will have serious trouble learning the higher level tools later.<br><br>I would hate to have any Shadow Knight get to the high level game and be a detriment to a raid because they didn't really understand their abilities.<br><br>A co-worker of mine once told me that there is a big difference between having 20 years of experience and having the same experience for 20 years.  I think that applies to any Shadow Knight who thinks that levels are more important than experience.<br><br>Good hunting friend...<br><br><br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Mon Oct 14 12:16:50 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br>Shrikke - Knight of Fear<br>Bristlebane</td></tr>
