	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Oct 10th 7:35 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.15]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I agree with the MoSS comment.&nbsp;&nbsp;Its a super low-to-mid lvl SK weapon and you can generally get it for dirt cheap.  Eventually, you can upgrade to Ebon Mace.<br><br>As far as a 2HS, I wouldnt waste your time getting Dark Reaver.  I think the proc doesnt take place until lvl 30 and even then the strength tap doesnt (to me) justify the decrease in delay and the increase in damage you could get from BABS (24/39, plus a buff or two).  BABS is also dirt cheap and would yield benefits immediately (well, to the extent the dmg cap will let you).<br><br>As far as armor goes, Dreadscale is the way to go if you dont have dinero.  If you want a quicker route, and have a little PP, then Ry'Gorr is a decent alternative (thought not as good to me).  Dreadscale is going to need to die in your late 40s / early 50s though.  I would change my focus to some of the Velious armor at that time (Thurg armor quests).<br><br>As far as Greenmist goes, I have studied it extensively and have come to the following conclusion:  ONLY do Greenmist if you do NOT plan on being in a decent to strong guild with this alt.  You can get Greenmist, which is a good weapon, but by no means whatsoever a great weapon, without being in a strong guild and that is its greatest benefit.  If you get into a decent guild, you will get weapons that will utterly dwarf Greenmist and Greenmist is a time consuming group of quests and one where you probably wont finish it until you are in your 50s at least.  <br><br>No Khurki pre-Greenmist is even worth wielding, so keep that in mind.<br><br>At present, Greenmist is really only good against Shissar, but even then it takes a back seat to Inn Curse.  Against non-shissar, it will barely outdamage Shard of Night, and even then it has to be on the proc to do so.  Granted, there are some other benefits of wielding it over Shard of Night, but I hope you can see my point; it just isnt a great weapon.  Believe me, I am really disappointed by it.<br><br>GL in your travels<br><br>Luna<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
