	   <tr><td colspan=2>Uhmmm...a treehugger on the Shadowknight board.&nbsp;&nbsp;Since you are playing an Iksar, I will not taunt you with comments about splinters :-)<br><br>You didn't mention what level you are at the moment.  I am going to assume less than 20th for the purposes of this discussion.<br><br>As far as weapons, I would suggest to set your sights on a Mace of the Shadow Souls(MoSS)(1HB)and A Dark Reaver(2HS).  The Bazaar has been known to have both of these weapons at amazingly low prices.  The other weapon I would look into is a Deathbringer's Rod(2HB)(30/40).  All of those weapons are SK only and tend to be sold at a low price. I would get rid of the Validus Sword (12/42 if I remember correctly) as soon as possible.  I know that your cash flow is low at the moment, but hang around Kurn's Tower and farm bone chips (5pp for a stack of 20) and you should be making some gains in that area.<br><br>For a 1HS, if you are wanting to save cash, do the Iksar Shadowknight weapon quests found at the SK guild.  The Quest of Pain is really annoying and a long camp, but is in an area where you can get experience at the same time.  And eventually, you will be questing for the legenary sword &quot;Greenmist&quot;.<br><br>As far as your armor...start buying banded whenever you see it.  By turning in your banded armor plus the appropriate quest items you can start getting Dreadscale Armor.  I got the breastplate at 21st level and still wear it at 45th (although I will be first to say I need an upgrade).<br><br>Welcome to a race/class combination with a great history.  Good hunting broodling.<br>&nbsp;<br>Shrikke - Knight of Fear<br>Bristlebane</td></tr>
